pter in Claude Welch, 'The Soldier and the State in Africa,' 1970.\n\n==References==\n* ''[[CIA World Factbook]], 2006''\n* {{cite book |last=Metz |first=Helen |date=1994 |title=Algeria: A Country Study |url=https://archive.org/details/nicaraguacountry00merr |location= |publisher=Federal Research Division, Library of Congress |isbn=0-8444-0831-X |accessdate=January 2015 |quote=\"5th Ed. Supersedes the 1986 edition of Algeria: A Country Study edited by Harold D. Nelson. Research completed December 1993.\" }}\n* ''U.S. Department of State Background Notes, 2003''\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090212172924/http://specialoperations.com/Foreign/Algeria/Default.htm SpecialForces.com: Algeria]\n* ''FIS, arm\u00e9e, GIA : vainqueurs et vaincus'', Riadh Sidaoui, \u00e9d. Publisud, Paris, 2002 {{cite web|url= http://bibmed.mmsh.univ-aix.fr/Syntheses_Biblio/mouvement_lat.pdf |title=Bibliographies sur les mouvements islamistes au Maghreb (Biblioth\u00e8que de la M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e) }}&nbsp;{{small|(285&nbsp;KB)}}\n\n{{Algeria topics}}\n{{Military of Africa}}\n{{Military of the Arab world}}\n{{Algeria Military}}\n{{Algerian security forces}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Military Of Algeria}}\n[[Category:Military of Algeria| ]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reword - you can't be \"among one\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algerian_People%27s_National_Armed_Forces"}
{"title_page": "Famous in Love", "text_new": "{{short description|2017 American drama television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Famous in Love\n| image                = Famous in Love title card.png\n| image_alt            = \n| genre                = [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n| based_on             = {{based on|''Famous in Love''|Rebecca Serle}}\n| developer            = [[I. Marlene King]]<br>Rebecca Serle\n| starring             = {{plainlist |\n* [[Bella Thorne]]\n* Charlie DePew\n* Georgie Flores\n* [[Carter Jenkins]]\n* Niki Koss\n* [[Keith Powers]]\n* Pepi Sonuga\n* [[Perrey Reeves]]\n}}\n| composer             = [[Michael Suby]]\n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 2\n| num_episodes         = 20\n| list_episodes        = #Episodes\n| executive_producer   = {{plainlist |\n* Dan Farah\n* Christopher Fife\n* Miguel Arteta\n* I. Marlene King\n}}\n| producer             = {{plainlist |\n* Tawnya Bhattacharya & Ali Laventhol\n* Hynndie Wali\n}}\n| cinematography       = Larry Reibman\n| camera               = [[Single-camera]]\n| runtime              = 38\u201342 minutes\n| company              = {{plainlist |\n* Long Lake\n* Carmina Productions\n* Farah Films\n* [[Warner Horizon Television]]\n}}\n| distributor          = [[Warner Bros. Television Distribution]]<ref name=\"Warner Bros\">{{cite web |url=https://www.warnerbros.com/tv/famous-love |title=Famous in Love |work=Warner Bros}}</ref>\n| network              = [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2017|4|18}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|2018|5|30}}\n| website              = http://freeform.go.com/shows/famous-in-love\n| production_website   = http://www.disneyabcpress.com/freeform/shows/famous-in-love/\n}}\n\n'''''Famous in Love''''' is an American [[Drama (film and television)|drama]] television series that premiered on [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] on April 18, 2017, and is based on the novel of the same name by Rebecca Serle. The series stars [[Bella Thorne]], Charlie DePew, Georgie Flores, [[Carter Jenkins]], Niki Koss, [[Keith Powers]], Pepi Sonuga, and [[Perrey Reeves]]. On June 29, 2018, Freeform announced that it had cancelled the series after two seasons.\n\n== Plot ==\nPaige Townsen, an ordinary college student, gets her big break after auditioning for the starring role in a Hollywood blockbuster and must now navigate her new star-studded life and undeniable chemistry with her co-lead and her best friend.\n\n== Cast and characters ==\n=== Main ===\n* [[Bella Thorne]] as Paige Townsen, a young college student who gets cast in the movie adaptation of a blockbuster book series called ''Locked'', which causes her life to change overnight. She has a choice between Jake (Charlie DePew) or Rainer (Carter Jenkins) and between dating Jake has a spark with Rainer.\n* Charlie DePew as Jake Salt, a down-to-earth guy from the Midwest with an edge who aspires to be a screenwriter and an indie filmmaker. He is Paige's best friend and one of her love interests. Charlie DePew replaced Jesse Henderson in the role from the original pilot.\n* Georgie Flores as Cassandra \"Cassie\" Perkins, Paige's roommate and close friend\n* [[Carter Jenkins]] as Rainer Devon, the son of famous producer Nina Devon, and, as later revealed, Alan Mills. He is labeled the \"sexiest man alive\", and is a famous actor. He has a complicated friendship with Jordan Wilder and soon develops a romantic interest in Paige Townsen.\n* Niki Koss as Alexis Glenn, Rainer's old friend who competes for the same role as Paige. She is secretly bisexual.\n* [[Keith Powers]] as Jordan Wilder, a troubled star who lands the role of the other point in the movie's famous love triangle. He and Rainer have a complicated history which is further heightened by the fact that both share a past with Tangey.\n* Pepi Sonuga as Tangey Turner, a pop star with a controlling mother. She was sleeping with Jordan Wilder while dating Rainer Devon, which creates tension between the two men.\n* [[Perrey Reeves]] as Nina Devon, Rainer's smart and cunning mother. Confident and manipulative, she will do whatever it takes to make sure things go her way.\n\n=== Recurring ===\n* [[Jason Antoon]] as Wyatt, the original director of the movie adaptation of ''Locked'', who leaves the production on the film during its two-month hiatus (season 1)\n* [[Nathan Stewart-Jarrett]] as Barrett, an entertainment and gossip reporter whose beat is Hollywood (season 1)\n* [[Shawn Christian]] as Alan Mills, the head of the film studio producing the movie\n* [[Vanessa A. Williams|Vanessa Williams]] as Ida, Tangey's mother and manager\n* Tom Maden as Adam, a production assistant on the movie and Cassie's boyfriend\n* [[Danielle Campbell]] as Harper, a former child star whom Rainer meets in rehab and with whom he quickly becomes involved (season 2)\n* [[Claudia Lee]] as Billy, an actress working as a waitress whom Jake hires to replace Paige as the lead on his independent film (season 2)\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Development ===\nFreeform, then known as ABC Family, had picked up the pilot for fast-track development on March 19, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2015/03/bella-thorne-famous-in-love-book-rebecca-serle-series-abc-family-1201395444/ |title=Bella Thorne to Star in ABC Family Drama Famous in Love from Marlene King |work=Deadline Hollywood |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |date=March 19, 2015 |access-date=July 11, 2016}}</ref> The pilot was shot in November 2015; Freeform [[greenlit]] the pilot on April 7, 2016,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/04/freeform-picks-up-famous-in-love-drama-pilot-to-series-bella-thorne-1201733402/ |title=Bella Thorne Drama Pilot Famous in Love Picked Up to Series by Freeform |work=Deadline Hollywood |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |date=April 7, 2016 |access-date=July 11, 2016}}</ref> and shooting began on July 13, 2016, and wrapped up on October 19, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |first=Charlie |last=DePew |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BLzJWj_AAvj/ |title=Wrapped season 1 of @famousinlovetv yesterday and I can't believe it's already done. I get to work with the coolest people in the business and I CANT WAIT for you all to see what we've been up to at good ol' Warner Brothers Studios. I was going to post a video of the cast doing the juju but @keithpowers makes us all look like amateurs so that one will have to wait. \ud83d\ude02 April 2017. The clock is ticking \u23f1 |via=[[Instagram]] |accessdate=December 14, 2017 |date=October 20, 2016}}</ref> On November 18, 2016, Freeform announced that the series would premiere on April 18, 2017. Freeform also released the entire season for viewing online on April 18, 2017. The series is based on the novel of the same name, written by Rebecca Serle. Serle worked with [[I. Marlene King]] to develop the novel into a television series.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/11/pretty-little-liars-final-season-premiere-date-famous-in-love-bella-thorne-freeform-1201857126/ |title=Pretty Little Liars Final Season & New Bella Thorne Drama Famous in Love Get Premiere Dates on Freeform |work=Deadline Hollywood |first=Erik |last=Pedersen |date=November 19, 2016 |access-date=November 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/pretty-little-liars-end-season-923990 |title=It's Official: Pretty Little Liars to End with Season 7 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |first=Lesley |last=Goldberg |date=August 29, 2016 |access-date=August 29, 2016}}</ref> Freeform renewed the series for a second season on August 3, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2017/08/famous-in-love-renewed-season-2-freeform-1202142127/ |title=Famous in Love Renewed for Season 2 by Freeform |work=Deadline Hollywood |first=Denise |last=Petski |date=August 3, 2017 |access-date=August 3, 2017}}</ref> The table read for the second season started on October 30, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Ba4ynROgL45/ |title=The @famousinlovetv season 2 table read was liTty today. I feel like the new kid at school! Truly blessed and excited for this journey. Ps: We're about to make some bomb a$ Tv for yall though. \ud83d\ude1c\ud83d\udca5\ud83d\udcfd |first=Romeo |last=Miller |via=[[Instagram]] |date=October 30, 2017 |access-date=December 14, 2017}}</ref> The second season premiered on Freeform on April 4, 2018.\n\nOn June 26, 2018, it was reported that Freeform had decided to cancel the series after Hulu declined to contribute more money towards the production of a third season. Clashes between actress [[Bella Thorne]] and showrunner I. Marlene King were also cited as part of the reason for the cancellation.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/famous-love-canceled-2-seasons-freeform-1123477/ |title='Famous in Love' Canceled After 2 Seasons on Freeform |work=The Hollywood Reporter |first=Lesley |last=Goldberg |date=June 26, 2018 |access-date=June 26, 2018}}</ref> On her Twitter account, King denied the claim of a feud between her and Thorne, and Freeform stated the show had yet to be cancelled.<ref>{{cite tweet |first=I. Marlene |last=King |user=imarleneking |number=1011775404619718656 |title=Despite what may be out there I am not in a feud w @bellathorne. We have, and have always had, a friendly and professional relationship. |accessdate=June 27, 2018 |date=June 26, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url=http://ew.com/tv/2018/06/26/famous-in-love-not-canceled-freeform/|title=Bella Thorne's 'Famous In Love' not yet canceled, Freeform says|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|last=Highfill|first=Samantha|date=June 26, 2018 |access-date=July 6, 2018}}</ref> On June 29, Freeform officially cancelled the series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2018/06/29/famous-in-love-cancelled-official-statement-season-3-freeform/ |title='Famous in Love' Officially Cancelled; Freeform Laments 'Difficult Decision' |work=TVLine |first=Andy |last=Swift |date=June 29, 2018 |access-date=July 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\n[[Romeo Miller]] was cast as Pablo $$ in a recurring role for the second season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2017/10/31/famous-in-love-season-2-spoilers-romeo-miller-cast/ |title=Famous in Love Courts Romeo Miller to Play Hip-Hop Superstar in Season 2 |work=TVLine |first=Andy |last=Swift |date=November 1, 2017 |access-date=November 13, 2017}}</ref> [[Sofia Carson]] appeared in multiple episodes of the second season as Sloane, the daughter of a movie mogul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2018/01/pretty-little-liars-the-perfectionists-sofia-carson-cast-freeform-drama-pilot-1202273265/ |title=Pretty Little Liars: The Perfectionists: Sofia Carson Cast in Freeform Drama Pilot |work=Deadline Hollywood |first=Denise |last=Petski |date=January 29, 2018 |access-date=January 29, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Episodes ==\n\n=== Series overview ===\n{{Series overview\n\n| color1    = #A52A2A\n| link1     = #Season 1 (2017)\n| episodes1 = 10\n| start1    = {{Start date|2017|4|18}}\n| end1      = {{End date|2017|6|13}}\n\n| color2    = #40E0D0\n| link2     = #Season 2 (2018)\n| episodes2 = 10\n| start2    = {{Start date|2018|4|4}}\n| end2      = {{End date|2018|5|30}}\n\n}}\n\n=== Season 1 (2017) ===\nThe entire first season was released on digital platforms, such as [[Video on demand|OnDemand]], the Freeform App and website, and [[Hulu]], on April 18, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/famous-in-love-freeform-full-season-binge-premiere-marlene-king-bella-thorne-1202005550/ |title=Freeform's Marlene King Series Famous in Love to Launch with Full-Season Binge |work=Variety |first=Elizabeth |last=Wagmeister |date=March 9, 2017 |access-date=April 18, 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table\n| background      = #A52A2A\n| overall         = \n| season          = \n| title           = \n| titleR          = <ref name=\"The Futon Critic\" /><r