ese citizen were evacuated by a flight operated by [[Mahan Air]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-evacuates-students-iraqis-syrians-from-china-coronavirus-epicenter/30418195.html |title=Iran Evacuates Students, Iraqis, Syrians From Coronavirus Epicenter |date=2020-02-04 |work=[[Radio Farda]] |accessdate=2020-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206132006/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-evacuates-students-iraqis-syrians-from-china-coronavirus-epicenter/30418195.html |archive-date=2020-02-06 }}</ref>\n|-\n|2020-02-04\n|{{USA}}\n|350 (est.)<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/350-evacuees-wuhan-coronavirus-epicenter-arrive-at-us-military-bases-2020-2 |title=350 more evacuees from Wuhan, the epicenter of the coronavirus outbreak, have arrived at US military bases for a 14-day quarantine |date=2020-02-05 |work=[[Business Insider]] |accessdate=2020-02-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205234840/https://www.businessinsider.com/350-evacuees-wuhan-coronavirus-epicenter-arrive-at-us-military-bases-2020-2 |archive-date=2020-02-05 }}</ref>\n|\n|[[Travis Air Force Base]]<br/>[[Marine Corps Air Station Miramar]]\n|There were two flights, one of which went to Travis AFB near San Francisco, and the other which refueled there and continued to MCAS Miramar near San Diego. Passengers on both flights were quarantined for 14 days. On February 10, one passegner was confirmed infected and became the 13th case in the United States.<ref>{{Cite web |title=First Coronavirus Case Confirmed in San Diego County |url=https://www.nbcsandiego.com/news/local/first-coronavirus-case-confirmed-in-san-diego-county/2261207/ |accessdate=2020-02-11 |work=NBC 7 San Diego |language=en-US |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200216075616/https://www.nbcsandiego.com/news/local/first-coronavirus-case-confirmed-in-san-diego-county/2261207/ |archive-date=2020-02-16 }}</ref>\n|-\n|2020-02-05\n|{{RUS}}\n|147\n|\n|[[Roshchino International A