y/202003290006|website=Focus Taiwan}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2020-04-01|title=Virus Outbreak: Taiwan shares evacuation flight|url=https://www.taipeitimes.com/News/taiwan/archives/2020/03/30/2003733650|website=Taipei Times}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020-03-30\n|\n|\n|{{Flagicon|CHN}}[[Shanghai Pudong International Airport]]\n|{{Flagicon|TWN}}[[Taoyuan International Airport]]\n| Two flights operated by [[China Airlines]] between Taoyuan and Shanghai will be opened to transport Taiwanese nationals in Hubei Province home.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2020-03-29|title=Taiwanese in Hubei can fly back on 2 CAL flights from Shanghai: SEF|url=https://focustaiwan.tw/cross-strait/202003260005|website=Focus Taiwan}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020-03-31\n|{{AUS}}\n|260\n|\n|{{Flagicon|PER}}[[Jorge Ch\u00e1vez International Airport|Lima International Airport]]\n|{{Flagicon|AUS}}[[Sydney International Airport]]\n| A group of about 260 Australians who paid at least $5,160 each for an evacuation flight out of Peru have returned home.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2020-03-31|title=Celebrations as Peru evacuation flight lands in Australia|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/news/celebrations-as-peru-evacuation-flight-lands-in-australia|website=SBS News}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020-03-31\n|{{ROK}}\n|309\n|\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} [[Milan Malpensa Airport]]\n|{{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Incheon International Airport]]\n|A [[Korean Air]] Charted flight brought 309 Korean from Milan to Incheon.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2020-04-01|title=S. Korean chartered plane returns with some 300 nationals from virus-hit Italy|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20200401007600325?section=search|website=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020-04-01\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{USA}}\n|\n|\n|{{Flagicon|COL}}[[El Dorado International Airport|Bogota El Dorado International Airport]]\n|{{Flagicon|USA}}[[Eglin Air Force Base]]\n|The U.S. Embassy, in conjunction with the U.S. Department of Defense, has organized an evacuation flight for U.S. citizens from El Dorado Airport in B