5 nationals from virus-hit Italy|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20200402007800325?section=search|website=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020-04-02\n|{{USA}}\n|\n|\n|{{Flagicon|COL}}[[El Dorado International Airport|Bogota El Dorado International Airport]]\n|{{Flagicon|USA}}[[Fort Lauderdale\u2013Hollywood International Airport]]\n| The U.S. Embassy announced that [[Spirit Airlines]] will operate a humanitarian flight from [[Bogota, Colombia]] on April 2, 2020. The flight will depart from El Dorado International Airport and arrive at Fort Lauderdale \u2013 Hollywood International Airport in Fort Lauderdale, Florida.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2020-04-01|title=Alert: Humanitarian Flight to Fort Lauderdale on April 2 Operated by Spirit Airlines|url=https://co.usembassy.gov/humanitarian-flight-on-spirit-airlines-2/|website=US Embassy in Colombia}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020-04-03\n|{{HKG}}\n|76\n|{{Flagicon|HKG}}65<br/>{{Flagicon|MYS}}6<br/>{{Flagicon|UK}}5\n|{{Flagicon|PER}}[[Alejandro Velasco Astete International Airport|Cusco International Airport]]<br />[[Jorge Ch\u00e1vez International Airport|Lima International Airport]]\n|{{Flagicon|UK}}[[London Heathrow International Airport]]\n| The Hong Kong Government has arranged a charted flight to bring 65 [[Hong Kongers]], 6 [[Malaysians]] and 5 [[Britons]] from Lima to London, then the Hong Kongers will go onboard a regular connecting flight with secured bookings from London to Hong Kong. For those Hong Kongers and Malaysians who are stranded in Cusco, they will also take a domestic charted flight arranged by the Hong Kong government flying to Lima.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2020-04-03|title=65 to take Peru flight|url=https://www.news.gov.hk/eng/2020/04/20200403/20200403_201104_568.html|website=new.gov.hk}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Controversies and issues==\n===Quarantine locations===\nAustralian Prime Minister [[Scott Morrison]] announced plans in late January 2020 to quarantine Australian citizens evacuated from Wuhan, including children and the elderly, for a period of 14 days on [[Christmas Island]]. The decision to repatriate those citizens using [[Christmas Island Detention Centre|controversial detention facilities]] formerly used to detain [[asylum seeker]]s before they were shut down in 2018 has received criticism.<ref name=20200129businessinsider>{{Cite web |url=https://www.businessinsider.com.au/wuhan-christmas-island-quarantine-coronavirus-2020-1 |title=The government will evacuate Australians trapped in Wuhan by the coronavirus outbreak and quarantine them on Christmas Island |last=Derwin |first=Jack |date=29 January 2020 |website=Business Insider Australia |access-date=31 January 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200131063430/https://www.businessinsider.com.au/wuhan-christmas-island-quarantine-coronavirus-2020-1 |archive-date=31 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Controversially, the government plan also necessitates those evacuees to pay a fee of A$1,000, and would take them to [[Perth]] after the quarantine period, where they would need to arrange their own transportation back to their home cities. The [[Australian Medical Association]], in a statement on the same day, stated that the decision to hold Australian citizens in \"a place where has been previously the focus of populations under enormous mental and physical trauma and anguish, is not a really appropriate solution.\"<ref name=20200131theguardian>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/jan/30/coronavirus-live-updates-china-death-toll-wuhan-evacuation-foreign-nationals-citizens-latest-news?page=with%3Ablock-5e325e3f8f086a28115a2132 |title=Virus death toll reaches 213 in China \u2013 as it happened |last=Gayle |first=Alison Rourke (now); Molly Blackall Damien |date=31 January 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=31 January 2020 |last2=Weaver |first2=Matthew |issn=0261-3077 |last3=Murray |first3=Jessica |last4=Rourke (earlier) |first4=Alison |last5=Doherty |first5=Ben |last6=Doherty |first6=Ben |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200131070209/https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/jan/30/coronavirus-live-updates-china-death-toll-wuhan-evacuation-foreign-nationals-citizens-latest-news?page=with%3Ablock-5e325e3f8f086a28115a2132 |archive-date=31 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn some places, local residents rallied against the decision to quarantine evacuees in their region. Residents of Nautana protested against the Indonesian government in early February 2020 for letting the evacuees stay there. Hundreds staged demonstrations and burned tires. As a result, [[Mobile Brigade Corps|Brimob]] and [[Indonesian National Armed Forces]] troops were deployed to ensure stable security conditions.<ref name=kompas18083841>{{Cite web|url=https://amp.kompas.com/regional/read/2020/02/01/18083841/warga-natuna-datangi-koramil-protes-karantina-wni-dari-wuhan |title=Warga Natuna Datangi Koramil, Protes Karantina WNI dari Wuhan|last=Maulana|first=Hadi |website=Kompas.com|language=id-ID|date=2 February 2020|access-date=3 February 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200203064822/https://amp.kompas.com/regional/read/2020/02/01/18083841/warga-natuna-datangi-koramil-protes-karantina-wni-dari-wuhan |archive-date=3 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> To protect and give health assurance to local people, Jokowi ordered Health Minister [[Terawan Agus Putranto]] to have a temporary office in Natuna.<ref name=tempo1302771>{{Cite web|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/1302771/jokowi-orders-health-minister-to-open-office-in-natuna |title=Jokowi Orders Health Minister to Open Office in Natuna|last=Bhwana|first=Petir Garda|date=3 February 2020|website=Tempo|access-date=3 February 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200203084604/https://en.tempo.co/read/1302771/jokowi-orders-health-minister-to-open-office-in-natuna |archive-date=3 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn the Philippines, the usage of the [[New Clark City]] development as a quarantine site was met with opposition from the municipal council of [[Capas]]. The local legislative said that they were not consulted by the national Department of Health and the [[Bases Conversion and Development Authority]] regarding the plan and suggested the national government to consider a more isolated area as a quarantine site.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tan |first1=Lara |title=Tarlac town opposes use of New Clark City as coronavirus quarantine site |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/2/7/Novel-coronavirus-New-Clark-City-Capas-Tarlac-quarantine.html |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nAfter healthy Ukrainian evacuees returned from Wuhan to Ukraine on 20 February 2020, [[Misinformation related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|misinformation]] caused riots as protestors railed against the decision to quarantine the passengers nearby the day after they flew back, and the evacuees' bus was attacked.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Coronavirus: Ukraine protesters attack buses carrying China evacuees |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51581805 |accessdate=2020-02-23 |date=2020-02-21 |work=[[BBC News]] |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222165035/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51581805 |archive-date=2020-02-22 |url-status=live |quote=On Thursday, 45 Ukrainians and 27 foreign nationals were flown from Wuhan in China, the epicentre of the deadly outbreak, to Kharkiv in eastern Ukraine.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first1=A. B. C.|last1=News|accessdate=2020-03-18|title=Hysteria over coronavirus sparks violent protests in Ukraine|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/hysteria-coronavirus-sparks-violent-protests-ukraine/story?id=69124337 |website=[[ABC News]] |quote=The evacuees -- 45 Ukrainians, 27 Argentinians and citizens from several other South American countries, as well as 22 crew members and doctors -- were flown to Ukraine from China's Hubei Province. All of them have already tested negative for the virus, authorities said, but are to be held in quarantine to ensure they aren't carrying it. |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200318220049/https://abcnews.go.com/International/hysteria-coronavirus-sparks-violent-protests-ukraine/story?id=69124337 |archivedate=18 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Improper procedures===\nA [[Department of Health and Human Services]] employee claimed that the workers who received Americans from the first evacuation from Wuhan were inadequately trained and equipped.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Lena H.|last1=Sun|first2=Yasmeen|last2=Abutaleb |accessdate=2020-03-24|title=U.S. workers without protective gear assisted coronavirus evacuees, HHS whistleblower says|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/health/2020/02/27/us-workers-without-protective-gear-assisted-coronavirus-evacuees-hhs-whistleblower-says/|website=Washington Post}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first1=Kristen Holmes, Amanda Watts and Caroline Kelly|last1=CNN|accessdate=2020-03-24|title=HHS whistleblower claims US workers received coronavirus evacuees without proper precautions|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/02/27/politics/hhs-whistleblower-coronavirus/index.html|website=CNN}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Evacuations related to the 2019-20 coronavirus pandemic}}\n[[Category:International responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Evacuations]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic-related lists]]\n", "name_user": "Orenburg1", "label": "safe", "comment": "sp", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evacuations_related_to_the_2019%E2%80%9320_coronavirus_pandemic"}
